      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BAREFOOT ELSA (4) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by a neck at this track in a handy 21.57 beating MULLIGRUB. Has good early speed so she should be prominent despite the squeeze draw. The one to beat again. MULLIGRUB (1) turned in a big run last time despite being beaten, finishing second in a Grade 3/4 behind BAREFOOT ELSA in a head turning 21.59 and clocking a new PB. Top run latest and can measure up here. INTEGRITY AL (2) was below best at his last couple, the latest finishing eighth at Casino, but was among the placings at Grafton three back. Has the ability and expected to do much better. MAGIC SHAZAM (7) has been in the money at her last two runs, most recently when third (21.89) in a Grade 3/4 over 390m at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw.",
